The paper discusses a distributed optimization algorithm for network consensus problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. The use of compressed information exchanges is a key feature of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses convergence analysis and performance comparisons, which are typical topics in Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on communication-efficient algorithms suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
